            section
                h1 la genèse

            p.
                The process of formal verification has following phases:
                1) model encoding,
                2) linking with base library of math components,
                3) desugaring to core functions,
                3) linking with pure base library, and
                4) extracting.
            p.
                <b>Minimal Model.</b> This model can serve HoTT research, being
                MLTT/CCHM prover with limited extraction of pure programs
                to certified interpreter.
            br.
